cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on a composite objective function that widely exists in machine learning, and proposes an algorithm that can scale well with the sample size and dimension simultaneously. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes an asynchronous parallel implementation with lock-free, which is more efficient than the one with writing or reading lock. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a stochastic block coordinate descent algorithm with the accelerated technology of variance reduction, which is a common optimization technique in algorithms. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the convergence rate of the proposed algorithm and provides theoretical analysis. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a parallel system with shared memory and discusses the speedup obtained on this system.
